    f.write('3. Add MAGIC to ResourceSystem as a standalone resource type\n')
    f.write('4. Create a lightweight InventorySystem for stackable items (consumables, crafting mats)\n')
    f.write('5. Wire InventorySystem into LootSystem pickups and ShopSystem buy/sell\n\n')
    f.write('This keeps the architecture consistent with the existing one-module-per-subsystem rule and avoids fragmenting item logic across multiple systems.\n')
